Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Re:  Keeper of drug house, 2nd & subsequent offense, on 07-16-22.
Order to report to TRPD for photo and prints
Commitment for Failure to Furnish Bail.

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of possess drug paraphernalia, PTC possess schedule II with intent to deliver, PTC possess schedule IV drug with intent to deliver, PTC possess methamphetamine with intent to deliver, PTC possess fentanyl with intent to deliver,  and keeper of drug house.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 07-25-22 at 1:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $1,000.00 cash bond with the conditions that he report to the Two Rivers Police Department for fingerprints, photographs and identifying information within 48 hours or, if incarcerated, within 72 hours of release, defendant is to have no contact with Nathan Kuklinski and Sabrina Duprey and defendant must maintain absolute sobriety.  Bail not furnished and defendant is remanded to the custody of the Sheriff.
